        'q' to "wa", 'w' to "qase", 'e' to "wrsd", 'r' to "etdf", 't' to "ryfg", 'y' to "tugh", 'u' to "yijh", 'i' to "uojk", 'o' to "ipkl", 'p' to "ol",
        'a' to "qwsz", 's' to "weadzx", 'd' to "ersfxc", 'f' to "rtdgcv", 'g' to "tyfhvb", 'h' to "yugjbn", 'j' to "uihknm", 'k' to "iojlm", 'l' to "opk",
        'z' to "asx", 'x' to "sdzc", 'c' to "dfxv", 'v' to "fgcb", 'b' to "ghvn", 'n' to "hjbm", 'm' to "jkn"
    )

    fun loadDictionary() {
        if (isLoaded) return
        Thread {
            try {
                loadUnigrams()
                loadBigrams()
                isLoaded = true
            } catch (e: Exception) {
                e.printStackTrace()
            }
        }.start()
    }

    private fun loadUnigrams() {
        val resId = context.resources.getIdentifier("dictionary", "raw", context.packageName)
        if (resId == 0) return
        context.resources.openRawResource(resId).use { stream ->
            stream.bufferedReader().forEachLine { line ->
                val parts = line.trim().split("\\s+".toRegex())
                if (parts.isNotEmpty()) {
                    val word = parts[0]
                    val freq = if (parts.size >= 2) parts[1].toLongOrNull() ?: 100L else 100L
                    insertTrie(word, freq)
                }
            }
        }
    }

    private fun loadBigrams() {
        val tempMap = HashMap<String, PriorityQueue<Pair<Long, String>>>()
        val resId = context.resources.getIdentifier("bigrams", "raw", context.packageName)
        if (resId == 0) return

        context.resources.openRawResource(resId).use { stream ->
            stream.bufferedReader().forEachLine { line ->
                val parts = line.trim().split(" ")
                if (parts.size >= 3) {
                    val w1 = parts[0].lowercase()
                    val w2 = parts[1]
                    val freq = parts[2].toLongOrNull() ?: 0L
                    if (freq > 1000) {
                        val heap = tempMap.getOrPut(w1) { PriorityQueue { a, b -> a.first.compareTo(b.first) } }
                        heap.add(freq to w2)
                        if (heap.size > 3) heap.poll()
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        tempMap.forEach { (key, heap) ->
            bigramMap[key] = heap.sortedByDescending { it.first }.map { it.second }
        }
    }

    fun learnWord(word: String) {
        insertTrie(word, Long.MAX_VALUE)
    }

    suspend fun predict(currentInput: String, previousWord: String, isAmharic: Boolean): List<String> {
        if (!isLoaded) return listOf("...")
        if (isAmharic) return emptyList()

        return withContext(Dispatchers.Default) {
            // 1. ZERO INPUT: Use Bigrams
            if (currentInput.isBlank()) {
                return@withContext bigramMap[previousWord.lowercase()] ?: listOf("The", "I", "Hello")
            }

            val term = currentInput.lowercase()
            val candidates = ArrayList<SearchResult>()

            // 2. BEAM SEARCH (Prefix / Autocomplete)
            // If I type "happ", I want "happy" first.
            val prefixes = searchPrefix(term)
            candidates.addAll(prefixes)

            // 3. FUZZY SEARCH (Correction)
            // Only run if we don't have enough perfect prefix matches, or if word is short
            if (candidates.size < 3) {
                val fuzzy = searchFuzzy(term)
                candidates.addAll(fuzzy)
            }

            // 4. RANKING
            // Sort by: Exact Match > High Freq Prefix > High Score Fuzzy
            candidates.sortedWith(Comparator { a, b ->
                // Exact match gets huge bonus
                val aExact = if (a.word.equals(term, true)) 1 else 0
                val bExact = if (b.word.equals(term, true)) 1 else 0
                if (aExact != bExact) return@Comparator bExact - aExact

                // Otherwise score
                b.score.compareTo(a.score)
            })
            .map { it.word }
            .distinct()
            .take(3)
        }
    }

    // === PREFIX SEARCH (Autocomplete) ===
    private fun searchPrefix(prefix: String): List<SearchResult> {
        var node = trieRoot
        for (c in prefix) {
            node = node.children[c] ?: return emptyList()
        }
        // Collect top descendants
        val results = ArrayList<SearchResult>()
        collectDescendants(node, prefix, results)
        return results
    }

    private fun collectDescendants(node: TrieNode, currentWord: String, results: MutableList<SearchResult>) {
        if (results.size >= 5) return // Optimization cap
        if (node.isEndOfWord && node.word != null) {
            // Prefix matches are "Pure", score = frequency
            results.add(SearchResult(node.word!!, node.frequency.toDouble()))
        }
        // Greedy walk: visit high freq children first
        node.children.values.sortedByDescending { it.maxSubtreeFreq }.forEach {
            collectDescendants(it, currentWord, results)
        }
    }

    // === FUZZY SEARCH ===
    private fun searchFuzzy(target: String): List<SearchResult> {
        val results = ArrayList<SearchResult>()
        val len = target.length

        // STRICT DYNAMIC COST
        val maxCost = when {
            len < 4 -> 1.0       // Short words: very strict
            len < 7 -> 2.0 
            else -> 3.0          // Long words: more lenient
        }

        recursiveWalk(trieRoot, target, 0, 0.0, maxCost, results)
        return results
    }

    private fun recursiveWalk(node: TrieNode, target: String, index: Int, cost: Double, maxCost: Double, results: MutableList<SearchResult>) {
        if (cost > maxCost) return

        // END OF WORD CHECK
        if (node.isEndOfWord && node.word != null) {
             val wordLen = node.word!!.length
             val lenDiff = abs(wordLen - target.length)

             // CRITICAL: Length Penalty
             // Prevent "knos" (4) -> "in" (2). 
             if (target.length < 5 && lenDiff > 1) return
             if (target.length >= 5 && lenDiff > 2) return

             val finalCost = cost + lenDiff
             if (finalCost <= maxCost) {
                 // Score = Frequency / (Cost+1)^3
                 // We dampen the frequency impact so huge common words don't override typed typos too easily
                 val score = node.frequency.toDouble() / Math.pow(finalCost + 1.0, 3.0)
                 results.add(SearchResult(node.word!!, score))
             }
        }

        // RECURSION
        // 1. INSERTION (User missed a char)
        // We move down the trie, but stay on target index
        if (cost + 1.0 <= maxCost) {
             node.children.forEach { (char, child) ->
                 // APOSTROPHE SPECIAL CASE: "wont" -> "won't"
                 val insertCost = if (char == '\'') 0.1 else 1.0
                 recursiveWalk(child, target, index, cost + insertCost, maxCost, results)
             }
        }

        if (index >= target.length) return
        val char = target[index]

        // 2. MATCH & SUBSTITUTION
        node.children.forEach { (childChar, childNode) ->
            var newCost = cost
            if (childChar != char) {
                // Mismatch
                val nearby = neighbors[char]?.contains(childChar) == true
                newCost += if (nearby) 0.5 else 1.0
            }
            recursiveWalk(childNode, target, index + 1, newCost, maxCost, results)
        }

        // 3. DELETION (User typed extra char)
        // We skip target char, stay on Trie Node
        recursiveWalk(node, target, index + 1, cost + 1.0, maxCost, results)
    }

    // DATA CLASSES
    data class SearchResult(val word: String, val score: Double)

    class TrieNode {
        val children = HashMap<Char, TrieNode>(4)
        var isEndOfWord = false
        var frequency: Long = 0
        var maxSubtreeFreq: Long = 0
        var word: String? = null
    }

    private fun insertTrie(word: String, freq: Long) {
        var node = trieRoot
        if (freq > node.maxSubtreeFreq) node.maxSubtreeFreq = freq
        for (c in word) {
            node = node.children.getOrPut(c) { TrieNode() }
            if (freq > node.maxSubtreeFreq) node.maxSubtreeFreq = freq
        }
        node.isEndOfWord = true
        node.word = word
        if (freq > node.frequency) node.frequency = freq
    }
}

